  "texts": [
    "Positional encoding, on the other hand, serves as a representation of the sequential order in which input words appear.",
    "For example, in NLP, the self-attention layers allow the model to learn long-range dependencies between words in a sentence.",
    "The functionality of self-attention layers involves the computation of scores for each word pair within the sentence which reflects the degree of interrelatedness between them.",
    "These computed scores are subsequently utilized to determine a weighted sum of input vectors, serving as the output of the self-attention layer.",
    "Concurrently, the positional encoding layer contributes crucial information regarding the position of each word in the sentence."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}